Sentencas: This paper presents the development of a new transient heat transfer model of a planar solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operating with humidified hydrogen.
Titulo: Transient heat transfer modeling of a solid oxide fuel cell operating with humidified hydrogen

Sentencas: The model is first validated with some benchmark test data and then used to simulate the transient behavior of the co- and counter-flow SOFCs at the heat-up and start-up stages.
Titulo: Transient heat transfer modeling of a solid oxide fuel cell operating with humidified hydrogen

Sentencas: In addition, a parametric study including the effects of Reynolds number at the fuel channel inlet and excess air coefficient on the output parameters is conducted.
Titulo: Transient heat transfer modeling of a solid oxide fuel cell operating with humidified hydrogen

Sentencas: The model predictions are found to be in very good agreement with the data published in the literature.
Titulo: Transient heat transfer modeling of a solid oxide fuel cell operating with humidified hydrogen

Sentencas: The transient simulations show that counter-flow SOFC yields higher performance, e.g. power density and electrical efficiency, but it needs slightly more time to reach the steady-state conditions.
Titulo: Transient heat transfer modeling of a solid oxide fuel cell operating with humidified hydrogen

Sentencas: The results of the parametric study point out that taking the Reynolds number low and excess air coefficient high gives higher electrical efficiencies for both of the configurations.
Titulo: Transient heat transfer modeling of a solid oxide fuel cell operating with humidified hydrogen

Sentencas: For the given input data, it is found that the counter-flow configuration has a higher electrical efficiency for low Reynolds numbers, e.g. 0.67 and all possible excess air coefficients.
Titulo: Transient heat transfer modeling of a solid oxide fuel cell operating with humidified hydrogen
